Material Information Summary – Proteomics International Laboratories Ltd (ASX: PIQ)

Capital Raising

  • Type: Share Purchase Plan (SPP) + Institutional Placement
  • Total Raised: $12 million (AUD) ($7.5m SPP, $4m institutional, $0.5m directors/KMP)
  • Use of Proceeds: Commercialisation of diagnostic tests (PromarkerD, Eso, Endo, OxiDx), US/AU lab expansions.

Operational & Financial Highlights (Appendix 4C)

  • Cash Balance (30 Jun 2025): $11.0 million (vs. $3.1m prior quarter).
  • Quarterly Cash Burn: Net operating outflow of $3.2m.
  • R&D Tax Incentive: ~$2 million expected in 1H FY25.
  • Customer Receipts: $201k (up from $84k prior quarter).

Key Commercial Milestones

  1. PromarkerD (Diabetic Kidney Disease):
  2. US Launch: Initiated at ADA Scientific Sessions; CPT PLA billing code (0579U) granted (effective 1 Oct 2025).
  3. Next-Gen Test: Simplified high-throughput immunoassay with 44-fold risk discrimination (AUC 0.88).

  4. AU Rollout: First sales achieved; partnership with Healius Group for national blood collection.

  5. PromarkerEso (Esophageal Cancer):

  6. Peer-reviewed validation: 91% sensitivity, 99% specificity.

  7. Planned launch at ISDE World Congress (Sep 2025).

  8. PromarkerEndo (Endometriosis):

  9. Clinical validation: 83% sensitivity, 95% specificity.

  10. Patent granted in Japan (first jurisdiction); AU launch targeted H2 CY25.

  11. OxiDx (Muscle Stress):

  12. Chinese patent granted; peer-reviewed study published for equine applications.

Other Material Updates

  • Funding Boost: $6m (WA Govt, Bioplatforms Australia, UWA) for lab infrastructure.
  • Cash Runway: ~3.5 quarters post-quarter (excludes $2m R&D rebate).

No material information omitted.

Material Information Summary

Drilling Results – Key Highlights

  • High-grade intersections from initial 13 holes:
  • 9m @ 2.63% Cu, 4.2% Zn, 0.12g/t Au, 5.6g/t Ag (within 21m @ 1.2% Cu, 2.3% Zn).
  • 6m @ 2.2% Cu, 3.0% Zn, 0.34g/t Au, 36.9g/t Ag.
  • 11m @ 1.6% Cu, 3.2% Zn, 0.15g/t Au, 4.1g/t Ag (within 54m @ 0.54% Cu, 1.5% Zn).
  • 27 holes completed (5,861m of planned 8,000m program).
  • 14 additional holes pending assays.
  • Diamond drilling planned for structural understanding.

Upcoming Catalysts

  • August 2025: Open-pit optimisation results (Scorpion deposit).
  • Pending: Updated resource estimate for Sulphide City.
  • Underground study for Sulphide City to assess high-grade potential.
  • Scoping study (combined Mt Chalmers/Develin Creek/Mt Mackenzie projects).

Mineral Resources (Develin Creek, March 2025):

  • Total MRE: 4.13Mt @ 1.01% Cu, 1.16% Zn, 0.15g/t Au, 6.0g/t Ag.
  • Indicated: 2.9Mt @ 1.09% Cu, 0.98% Zn.
  • Inferred: 1.3Mt @ 0.81% Cu, 1.58% Zn.

Material Information Summary

  • Drilling Highlights:
  • Diamond drilling commenced to extend high-grade mineralisation in hole 25PRC206, which ended in 23.5 g/t Au (12m @ 12.49 g/t Au, incl. 5m @ 27.93 g/t Au).

  • Mineralisation remains open 180m vertically and 40m west, supported by strong DHEM conductors.

  • DHEM Validation:

  • Strong conductor (Plate C9, 100m x 50m) confirms pyrrhotite-associated gold, guiding further exploration.

  • Multilateral drilling planned from 25PRC206 collar to test multiple targets efficiently.

  • Funding:

  • $144,500 co-funded EIS grant (WA DEMIRS) being used for additional high-priority drilling.

  • Resource Context:

  • Current MRE: 250koz Au @ 3.1 g/t (Paris, HHH, Observation deposits), open along strike and depth.

  • New mineralisation confirmed 240m west of existing resource.

  • Regional Potential:

  • 57km strike length largely untested; project near Westgold’s Beta Hunt and St Ives Goldfields.

Material Information Summary:

  • Metallurgical Testwork Results (Gradina Deposit, Rogozna Project):
  • Gold recoveries up to 97.9% (average 89.9%) using standard flotation methods.
  • Confirms viability of gold-pyrite concentrate production, with average concentrate grade of 26.1 g/t Au.

  • Exploration Update:

  • Ongoing drilling (8 rigs total): 4 rigs at Gradina targeting maiden Mineral Resource Estimate (MRE) by late 2025.

  • Mineral Resource Context (Rogozna Project):

  • Total inferred resources: 7.40Moz AuEq across Gradina, Shanac, Medenovac, and Copper Canyon deposits.
